'''Jeremy Cornelis Jacobus Antonisse''' (born 29 March 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|left winger]] for [[Super League Greece|Greek Super League]] club [[A.E. Kifisia F.C.|A.E. Kifisia]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|571721}}</ref>

==Club career==
A youth academy graduate of [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], Antonisse signed his first professional contract with the club in August 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=ANTONISSE WIL SCHITTEREN BIJ PSV|url=https://www.psv.nl/nieuwspagina/artikel/antonisse-wil-schitteren-bij-psv.htm|access-date=13 January 2021}}</ref> He signed a three-year contract through to the summer of 2022.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosmalens talent Jeremy Antonisse tekent tot 2022 bij PSV|url=https://www.bd.nl/psv/rosmalens-talent-jeremy-antonisse-tekent-tot-2022-bij-psv~aea015ea/|access-date=13 January 2021}}</ref>

On 30 November 2020, Antonisse made his professional debut for [[Jong PSV]] in a 1–0 league defeat to [[SC Cambuur]].<ref>{{cite web|title=PSV U21 SLIP TO 1-0 DEFEAT AGAINST LEADERS SC CAMBUUR|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/psv-u21-slip-to-1-0-defeat-against-leaders-sc-cambuur.htm|access-date=13 January 2021|archive-date=22 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210522122905/https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/psv-u21-slip-to-1-0-defeat-against-leaders-sc-cambuur.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his senior debut for PSV on 26 January 2021 in a 2–0 [[Eredivisie|league]] win against [[FC Emmen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Late treffers voorkomen gezichtsverlies van PSV bij hekkensluiter Emmen|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2366132-late-treffers-voorkomen-gezichtsverlies-van-psv-bij-hekkensluiter-emmen|date=26 January 2021|access-date=24 August 2021}}</ref> On 23 August 2021, he signed a contract extension with club until June 2024.<ref>{{cite web|title=PSV en aanvaller Jeremy Antonisse onderstrepen samenwerking met lang contract|url=https://www.ed.nl/psv/psv-en-aanvaller-jeremy-antonisse-onderstrepen-samenwerking-met-lang-contract~a63bc486/|date=23 August 2021|access-date=24 August 2021}}</ref> On 31 January 2023, he joined [[FC Emmen]] on a loan deal until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=FC Emmen huurt Jeremy Antonisse van PSV|url=https://www.rtvdrenthe.nl/sport/15318149/fc-emmen-huurt-jeremy-antonisse-van-psv|date=31 January 2023|access-date=4 February 2023}}</ref>

On 1 September 2023, [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] announced the signing of Antonisse on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Jeremy Antonisse chega para o ataque |trans-title=Jeremy Antonisse arrives for the attack |url=https://www.moreirensefc.pt/noticias/jeremy-antonisse-chega-para-o-ataque/ |access-date=3 September 2023 |website= |publisher=Moreirense FC |language=pt-PT}}</ref> In July 2025, he joined newly promoted [[Super League Greece|Greek Super League]] club [[A.E. Kifisia F.C.|A.E. Kifisia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Antonisse deixou o Moreirense e foi apresentado na Grécia|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/1630103751/antonisse-deixou-o-moreirense-e-foi-apresentado-na-grecia/|language=pt|date=28 July 2025|access-date=29 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Antonisse is of Curaçaoan descent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremy Antonisse: talento olandese classe 2002|url=https://www.worldfootballscouting.com/schede-giovani-talenti/jeremy-antonisse-talento-olandese-classe-2002/|access-date=13 January 2021}}</ref> He has previously represented Netherlands at youth level.<ref>{{cite web|title=Oud-jeugdspeler OJC Jeremy Antonisse met Oranje -17 naar Portugal|url=https://www.ed.nl/den-bosch/oud-jeugdspeler-ojc-jeremy-antonisse-met-oranje-17-naar-portugal~aa5c951c/|access-date=13 January 2021}}</ref> On 16 October 2019, he was named in stand-by list for the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SELECTIE ONDER 17 VOOR WK IN BRAZILIË|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/jeugd-mannen-onder-18/77059/selectie-onder-18-voor-wk-brazili%C3%AB|access-date=13 January 2021}}</ref>

In March 2021, Antonisse received his first call-up to the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] matches.<ref>{{cite web|title=HIDDINK MAAKT SELECTIE CURAÇAO BEKEND: ANITA EN ANTONISSE ERBIJ|url=https://eredivisie.nl/nl-nl/nieuwsbericht/hiddink-maakt-selectie-cura-ao-bekend--anita-en-antonisse-erbij|date=9 March 2021|access-date=14 March 2021|archive-date=23 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523083551/https://eredivisie.nl/nl-nl/nieuwsbericht/hiddink-maakt-selectie-cura-ao-bekend--anita-en-antonisse-erbij|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut on 25 March in a 5–0 win over [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines national football team|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremy Antonisse debuteert met assist voor Curaçao in doelpuntrijke wedstrijd|url=https://psv.supporters.nl/nieuws/artikel/48576/Jeremy-Antonisse-debuteert-met-assist-voor-Cura%C3%A7ao-in-doelpuntrijke-wedstrijd|date=26 March 2021|access-date=24 August 2021}}</ref> In June 2021, he was named in Curaçao's 42-man preliminary squad for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Curaçao probeert twee Feyenoorders weg te kapen bij Oranje|url=https://voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=389952|date=18 June 2021|access-date=24 August 2021}}</ref>

In June 2025, Antonisse was named in the squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosters confirmed for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/news/rosters-confirmed-for-2025-concacaf-gold-cup/|date=5 June 2025|access-date=11 June 2025}}</ref> In May 2026, he was named in Curaçao's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], the country's first-ever appearance at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Smallest nation Curacao name debut World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c70798249j0o|date=18 May 2026|access-date=18 May 2026}}</ref>

